Husbands should not only make their wives comfortable when they are breastfeeding their new born babies but should also abstain from incessant love making, a medical practitioner has said. The director of public health in Cross River State, Dr Iwara Iwara,said in Calabar  yesterday while speaking during a one-day media round table to consolidate on the gains of the World Breastfeeding Week. Dr Iwara who advocated paternity leave for men to enable them assist to their lactating wives called for extension of maternity leave to six months. He said husbands have usually had all the time with their wives before the delivery of the new born but as soon as the babies come in they must be given total and adequate attention, care and steady breastfeeding. More women adopt exclusive breastfeeding in Kebbi Sustaining the practice of breastfeeding Our husbands aren’t feeding us well, Kaduna wives claim Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin